{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how AC1 proof command coverage of all four topics will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["fc5753f10570a2f70","fe9da58eaf2876ed1","f263b01ce558c2136"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"AC1 proof command coverage of all four topics"},{"coaching":"Plan how AC3 shell-quoting defect in proving command will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f4ff1dda2b4e25aa5"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"AC3 shell-quoting defect in proving command"},{"coaching":"Pin down fate of CREATE-row entry after session_log promotion with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fc6ea94700509c5fa","f234c1af95b088972"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"fate of CREATE-row entry after session_log promotion"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] gate-interaction paragraph anchor in concurrency.md I4a will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f37919f6f4c4e4184","f27466343fbf4e90a"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"gate-interaction paragraph anchor in concurrency.md I4a"},{"coaching":"Weigh at least one structural alternative for boundary between add-wins caveat and event-body restatement.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f453a41c8e92c5e64"],"move_id":"5","move_name":"weigh alternatives","subject":"boundary between add-wins caveat and event-body restatement"},{"coaching":"Plan how AC4 verification of cross-reference to config.md will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f61854f27b68a7a8b","f58a84c21750c26f2"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"AC4 verification of cross-reference to config.md"},{"coaching":"Propagate the revision for dangling session-log pointer in architecture.md to the child tickets.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f19a104eb12bf36a2","f927a93cb24560928"],"move_id":"11","move_name":"propagate to children","subject":"dangling session-log pointer in architecture.md"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":11,"blocking":2,"dropped":5,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":6,"ran":true,"references":6,"resolved":5,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":1},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":3686,"file_impact":4,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":38,"verify_lint_abstained":38},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":936,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":4,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":200.3,"llm_calls":28,"llm_ms":527246.4,"total_ms":527554.1,"verify_requests":35},"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Replace the single-alternation `rg -c` in AC1 with four separate presence checks, one per topic, so each concept is independently verified (e.g. `rg -q 'parent_id' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'discovered_from\\|link' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'idea' docs/ticket-model.md`).","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md\" -ge 4","Taxonomy item 5: missing cardinality assertion when criterion names a count (four distinct topics)"],"finding":"AC1's proving command uses `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md` with a single alternation pattern; `rg -c` counts total lines matching ANY of the alternatives, not one per pattern. A document mentioning only `idea` four times would return count≥4 and pass, even if `parent_id`, `discovered_from`, and `set-tags` are completely absent — leaving three of the four required concept topics unverified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc5753f10570a2f70","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC1 proving command","norm_id":"nc8dd670723e293e7","priority":1.0,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["An executor writes a file covering only the `idea` lifecycle in depth (4+ lines) and omits hierarchy/parent_id, the six link relations, and tags — the AC still passes."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"rg -q 'idea' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'parent_id' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'discovered_from' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'event-schema' docs/ticket-model.md","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Strengthen AC1's proving command to assert each of the four key terms appears at least once individually, e.g.: `rg -q 'idea' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'parent_id' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'discovered_from' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'event-schema' docs/ticket-model.md`","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["The grep command uses `-c` (line count, not match count) with an OR pattern — four matching lines containing only 'idea' satisfy the ≥4 condition","The What section names four distinct required topics: (1) idea lifecycle, (2) hierarchy/containment (parent_id), (3) linking (six relations + promotion concept), (4) tags surface + --set-tags caveat","The AC does not assert that each of the four terms appears at least once, only that total line count ≥ 4"],"finding":"AC1's grep proof (`rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md` ≥ 4) is satisfiable by four hits of the single term `idea` (or any one term). It does not verify that all four named concept topics (idea lifecycle, hierarchy/containment via parent_id, linking via discovered_from, tags via set-tags) are each present as distinct documented topics — the AC would pass if three of the four topics are entirely absent but `idea` appears four times.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe9da58eaf2876ed1","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC1 — 'Proving: test -f docs/ticket-model.md && [ \"$(rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md)\" -ge 4 ]'","norm_id":"n2ea243f162bd790e","priority":1.0,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["An executor writes a ticket-model.md that thoroughly covers the idea lifecycle (many occurrences) but omits parent_id/hierarchy entirely — AC1 still passes","A reviewer running the AC proof sees 'PASS' but the doc is missing an agent-critical concept (hierarchy/containment or the six link relations)"],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace the single `-c … -ge 4` check with five separate `rg -q` assertions (one per required term/topic) chained with `&&`, so each topic is independently gated.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Strengthen the AC1 proof to verify each of the four topic terms appears at least once, e.g., `rg -q 'idea' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'parent_id' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'discovered_from' docs/ticket-model.md && rg -q 'set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md`.","cohort":["E3","E5","G5"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Proof: `rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md` with `-ge 4`","The regex is an OR match; ≥4 lines containing only 'idea' would satisfy the count threshold while omitting parent_id, discovered_from, and set-tags sections.","The AC text says 'documents all four concept topics' but the grep does not enforce 'all four'."],"finding":"AC1's shell proof (`rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md -ge 4`) counts lines matching ANY of the four terms, not that all four topics are substantively present. A file covering only 'idea' extensively (≥4 lines) with no mention of parent_id, discovered_from, or set-tags would still pass the grep while missing three of the four required topics.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f263b01ce558c2136","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria, AC1 — Proving shell command","norm_id":"nb1ced98724d4217c","priority":1.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An agent writes ticket-model.md with a detailed 'idea status' section (4+ lines) but omits the hierarchy/containment or linking sections; the AC1 proof passes but the goal is not met."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace the `-c` count check with four separate `rg -q` checks joined by `&&`, one per required topic term, so each topic must be individually present.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Fix the shell-quoting defect in the AC3 proving command by using single quotes for the inner rg pattern: `rg -q '## The session_log ticket type' docs/event-schema.md && [ \"$(rg -c 'see CLAUDE.md.*Session logs' docs/event-schema.md)\" = 0 ]`.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"$(rg -c \\\"see CLAUDE.md .Session logs\\\" docs/event-schema.md)\\\"\" — double-quote nesting inside $(...)","Taxonomy item 2: shell-expansion leakage / quoting defect"],"finding":"AC3's proving command embeds a `rg -c` invocation inside double quotes that itself contains double quotes, producing a shell-quoting defect: `[ \"$(rg -c \"see CLAUDE.md .Session logs\" docs/event-schema.md)\" = 0 ]` — the inner double quotes terminate the outer double-quoted string before `see CLAUDE.md`, causing a syntax error or mis-parsed arguments at execution time.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4ff1dda2b4e25aa5","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC3 proving command","norm_id":"nceb6c06c1f2bb611","priority":0.875,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An agent runs the proving command verbatim and gets a shell syntax error or silently tests the wrong pattern, reporting a false-pass or false-fail for the 'no longer defers to CLAUDE.md' half of AC3."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"rg -q '## The session_log ticket type' docs/event-schema.md && [ \"$(rg -c 'see CLAUDE.md.*Session logs' docs/event-schema.md)\" = 0 ]","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add to AC3 (or the What bullet for event-schema.md) an explicit disposition for the CREATE row's inline session_log description: either trim it to a one-line summary with a cross-ref to the new `## The session_log ticket type` section, or leave it verbatim (and accept the duplication) — making the executor's task unambiguous.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["event-schema.md line 46 CREATE row currently contains: '**`session_log`** is a verbose-log type that is gate/lifecycle-exempt, excluded from the graph/health compiles (via `reduce_all_tickets(exclude_session_logs=…)`) and default `list`, never synced to Jira, and refuses `STATUS` (no claim/transition) — see CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\"'","AC3 only specifies: add the new section AND remove the CLAUDE.md pointer — it is silent on whether to trim the CREATE row's inline description","Plan Design decisions: 'not a bulk move' — suggesting minimal changes, which implies the inline description stays, creating duplication"],"finding":"AC3 instructs removing the 'see CLAUDE.md Session logs' pointer from the CREATE row and adding a `## The session_log ticket type` section, but does not specify whether the CREATE row's existing ~1.5-line inline session_log behavioral description should be trimmed. Left as-is alongside the new dedicated section, event-schema.md will have two co-present descriptions of session_log semantics in the same file — the exact drift risk the plan claims to eliminate.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc6ea94700509c5fa","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC3 — 'docs/event-schema.md gains a ## The session_log ticket type section AND no longer defers session_log semantics to CLAUDE.md'; docs/event-schema.md line 46","norm_id":"nde31b8d839694ca5","priority":0.5025,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Executor adds the new section, removes the CLAUDE.md pointer, leaves the inline CREATE-row description intact → two session_log descriptions in event-schema.md","A future update to one description misses the other, producing inconsistent session_log semantics within the same file"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Extend AC3's prose: 'The CREATE row's existing inline session_log description should be reduced to a one-line tag plus cross-reference (e.g. \"a verbose-log type — see § The session_log ticket type below\") so a single authoritative description exists within the file.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan says to 'promote the existing CREATE-row note into a real section' in `docs/event-schema.md` for `session_log`, but gives no instruction about the fate of the source CREATE-row entry. The CREATE row (event-schema.md line 46) is a dense, multi-sentence inline spec covering gate-exemption, lifecycle-exemption, graph exclusion, STATUS refusal, link restrictions, Jira exclusion, and the title convention. Without specifying whether the row is shortened, left as-is, or partially replaced by a pointer to the new section, an executor will either produce duplicate content (drift risk the plan explicitly wants to avoid) or silently strip the row's forward-compat/reducer context.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f234c1af95b088972","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section / docs/event-schema.md — session_log section promotion","norm_id":"naa90baa9c16fbe28","priority":0.5025,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify in the What section the structural form of the gate-interaction addition to concurrency.md I4a: e.g. 'add a new `#### Gate interaction (plan-review gate on cascaded claims)` subsection after the existing `#### Cross-agent race ownership policy` subsection, covering [the three rules]' — so the executor knows the exact slot.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan What: 'Fold CLAUDE.md's cascade gate-interaction paragraph into docs/concurrency.md I4a, which already documents the cascade itself'","docs/concurrency.md I4a already has '#### Cross-agent race ownership policy (two agents, one open parent)' as a peer structural element","AC2 proof: rg -n 'gate-exempt|plan-review gate|--force' docs/concurrency.md — verifies term presence only, not structural placement","CLAUDE.md:458-467 contains the source gate-interaction paragraph — it cross-references the claim gate config key and the --force audit note"],"finding":"The plan says fold the CLAUDE.md gate-interaction paragraph ('The cascaded parent claim is a full claim — so it runs the parent's own plan-review claim gate; epics/stories are NOT gate-exempt; `--force` propagates up the cascade') into docs/concurrency.md I4a, but does not specify a structural placement (e.g. a named `####` subsection, or inline after a specific paragraph). I4a already has a peer `#### Cross-agent race ownership policy` subsection. AC2's proof grep (`rg -n 'gate-exempt|plan-review gate|--force'`) only verifies term presence, not co-location with the cascade schema. An executor has no guidance on HOW to structure the addition.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f37919f6f4c4e4184","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Fold CLAUDE.md's cascade gate-interaction paragraph into docs/concurrency.md I4a'; AC2","norm_id":"n8bb0b5b3d691b959","priority":0.2063,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Executor folds the gate-interaction text inline as a paragraph in I4a, making it hard to find for agents reading the cascade section","Executor creates a new '#### Gate interaction (plan-review gate on cascaded claims)' subsection — but this is not specified and different executors will choose differently","The --force mention in the concurrency doc conflicts with the existing I4a text (which doesn't mention --force) without a merge instruction"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify in the What section what ticket-model.md says about the `--set-tags` add-wins caveat vs. what it delegates to event-schema.md: e.g. 'explain the user-visible effect (add-wins on concurrent set-tags) and the `--set-tags`-compiles-to-delta semantics; delegate the TAG_DELTA event body format to event-schema.md' — so the executor knows exactly where the split falls.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan What section: 'the tags surface + the `--set-tags` add-wins caveat'","Plan What section: 'Cross-reference docs/event-schema.md for write-level event mechanics — do not restate event bodies (drift risk)'","docs/event-schema.md TAG_DELTA row (line 49): '`--set-tags` is compiled to a delta vs observed tags (add-wins)'","The add-wins caveat is a property of the TAG_DELTA event body — it cannot be explained conceptually without referencing event body semantics"],"finding":"The What section instructs ticket-model.md to cover 'the tags surface + the `--set-tags` add-wins caveat' while simultaneously prohibiting restating event bodies ('cross-reference docs/event-schema.md for write-level event mechanics — do not restate event bodies'). The add-wins caveat is defined exclusively inside the TAG_DELTA event-body row ('`--set-tags` is compiled to a delta vs observed tags … add wins on an intra-event conflict'). No resolution rule is given for where the conceptual line falls — an executor cannot satisfy both constraints without an authoritative split.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f453a41c8e92c5e64","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'docs/ticket-model.md' bullet; Design decisions section","norm_id":"na4c30f4f1a839530","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Executor writes the add-wins explanation in ticket-model.md, creating a second copy of event-body semantics that can drift from event-schema.md","Executor writes only 'see event-schema.md for add-wins' in ticket-model.md, making the concept doc uninformative on a stated topic","Future edits update the TAG_DELTA row but miss the ticket-model.md copy, producing silent semantic drift — exactly the risk the plan warns against"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add one sentence to the What bullet: 'The concept doc names the user-visible effect (concurrent `--set-tags` calls add-win; no tags are lost) and notes that `--set-tags` is compiled internally to an add/remove delta — the event-body format (TAG_DELTA `{added[], removed[]}`) is delegated to `docs/event-schema.md` with a cross-reference.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Extend AC4's verify (or add a separate check) to confirm that user-guide.md also contains a reference to `config.md` or `session-id-shims.md`, covering the cross-reference described in the What section.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["What: 'Cross-reference the session-id resolver already documented in `docs/config.md` (§ ~429-434).'","AC4 verify: `rg -n 'auto-rotat|current_session_log' docs/user-guide.md` — tests only for rotation terms, not for the cross-reference."],"finding":"The What section describes adding a cross-reference from user-guide.md to config.md (§ ~429-434) / session-id-shims.md alongside the auto-rotation detail, but AC4's verify (`rg -n 'auto-rotat|current_session_log' docs/user-guide.md`) only checks for the rotation content — the cross-reference to config.md is described work with no covering criterion.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f61854f27b68a7a8b","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section (session-log auto-rotation paragraph) vs AC4","norm_id":"n72f6d1c00527a6d6","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer adds the auto-rotation paragraph but omits the config.md cross-reference; AC4 passes but the described cross-reference is missing, creating the exact drift risk the plan calls out."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a second rg check to AC4: `rg -q 'config\\.md\\|session-id-shims' docs/user-guide.md` so the cross-reference is verified alongside the rotation content.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify that the 'cascade gate-interaction' content (plan-review gate nuance, gate-exemption for epics/stories, --force propagation) is correctly targeted at docs/concurrency.md I4a rather than docs/plan-review-gate.md, and update the plan's target section accordingly if the concepts don't belong alongside open→in_progress status-cascade invariants.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'Fold CLAUDE.md's cascade gate-interaction paragraph into docs/concurrency.md I4a, which already documents the cascade itself.'","AC proof: 'rg -n \\'gate-exempt|plan-review gate|--force\\' docs/concurrency.md'","Probe of concurrency.md I4a (lines 97–153): zero occurrences of 'gate-exempt', 'plan-review gate', '--force', or any plan-review gate concept; I4a covers only open→in_progress status-cascade semantics.","docs/plan-review-gate.md exists as a separate document that is the natural home for plan-review gate semantics."],"finding":"The plan asserts that I4a ('which already documents the cascade itself') is the correct anchor for the 'cascade gate-interaction paragraph' covering plan-review gates, gate-exemption for epics/stories, and --force propagation. But probing I4a (concurrency.md lines 97–153) shows it is entirely about the open→in_progress status-cascade with zero mention of plan-review gates, gate-exempt status, or --force. The AC proof-command (`rg -n 'gate-exempt|plan-review gate|--force' docs/concurrency.md`) currently returns 0 hits — which the plan acknowledges is the pre-state — but the scoping assertion 'I4a already documents the cascade context' is misleading: the gate-interaction content is conceptually distinct (plan-review gates, not status-cascade) and may belong more naturally in docs/plan-review-gate.md than in a concurrency invariant section. The false premise could cause the implementer to insert plan-review-gate semantics into a section whose readers expect only concurrency/locking invariants.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f27466343fbf4e90a","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What / 'Fold CLAUDE.md's cascade gate-interaction paragraph into docs/concurrency.md I4a' and AC line 2","norm_id":"nfa26bcc316b7cdd9","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer reading I4a as the target section adds plan-review gate content to a concurrency-invariants doc, creating a reader confusion mismatch (readers of concurrency.md expect locking/ordering invariants, not gate policy).","Future readers of concurrency.md I4a are surprised to find plan-review gate semantics mixed into a section titled 'Parent-first claim/transition cascade (open → in_progress)'."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Probe CLAUDE.md's cascade gate-interaction paragraph to determine whether the content is about (a) how the status-cascade interacts with the plan-review gate or (b) concurrency/locking. If (a), the authoritative home is docs/plan-review-gate.md (not I4a). If genuinely both, add a cross-reference from I4a rather than embedding gate-policy prose inside a concurrency-invariant section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add `docs/architecture.md` to the edit-set (or acknowledge the stale reference): update line 65's 'see CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\"' to point to the new `docs/event-schema.md#the-session_log-ticket-type` section once that section is created.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["docs/architecture.md line 65: 'leave it off so logs stay discoverable (see CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\").'","Plan scope: 'In: docs/ticket-model.md (new) and docs/{event-schema,concurrency,user-guide,README}.md' — architecture.md is not listed.","Once the authoritative home moves to event-schema.md, the architecture.md pointer to CLAUDE.md becomes a stale second-class reference."],"finding":"docs/architecture.md:65 contains 'see CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\"' — an in-repo consumer of the same CLAUDE.md session-log content being rehomed into event-schema.md. After this plan's changes, architecture.md will still point to CLAUDE.md rather than the new authoritative docs/event-schema.md section. This unenumerated consumer is outside the plan's stated edit-set.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f19a104eb12bf36a2","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section / docs/architecture.md:65","norm_id":"nbd734fa6dd239b53","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A reader following the architecture.md reference lands in CLAUDE.md (which the companion S2 plan may eventually slim), rather than the new authoritative event-schema.md section.","If S2 later removes session-log content from CLAUDE.md, architecture.md:65's reference becomes a dead pointer."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add docs/architecture.md to the Scope 'In' list and include a targeted edit: replace 'see CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\"' at line 65 with 'see [event-schema.md § session_log ticket type](event-schema.md#the-session_log-ticket-type)'.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add `docs/architecture.md` to the plan's scope (or explicitly acknowledge and defer it) so the `see CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\"` reference at line 65 is updated to point to the new `docs/event-schema.md#the-session_log-ticket-type` section rather than left dangling after S2.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["docs/architecture.md line 65: 'leave it off so logs stay discoverable (see CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\").'","Plan Scope section: 'In: docs/ticket-model.md (new) and docs/{event-schema,concurrency,user-guide,README}.md' — architecture.md is not listed.","Plan AC3: 'docs/event-schema.md gains a ## The session_log ticket type section AND no longer defers session_log semantics to CLAUDE.md' — but makes no mention of architecture.md's identical deferral."],"finding":"The plan fixes the `event-schema.md:46` 'see CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\"' pointer but does not address the identical dangling reference at `docs/architecture.md:65` ('see CLAUDE.md \"Session logs\"'). After CLAUDE.md is eventually slimmed (S2), architecture.md will still point to content that no longer lives there, leaving the fix incomplete.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f927a93cb24560928","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section / docs/architecture.md:65","norm_id":"n7dd980a7a0a3afad","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["S2 slims CLAUDE.md's 'Session logs' section; architecture.md:65 now points to absent content, breaking the reader's navigation path.","A contributor following the architecture.md reference for session_log exclusion behaviour finds the target gone."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add `docs/architecture.md` to the 'In:' scope line and add an AC: 'docs/architecture.md line ~65 no longer defers to CLAUDE.md for session_log semantics; points to docs/event-schema.md instead.' Proving: `rg -c 'see CLAUDE.md' docs/architecture.md` returns 0.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The What section describes adding a cross-reference from docs/user-guide.md to docs/config.md ('cross-referencing docs/config.md for the fingerprint resolver'), but no acceptance criterion verifies that this cross-reference was actually added.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f58a84c21750c26f2","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('cross-referencing docs/config.md for the fingerprint resolver') and AC#5","norm_id":"n2da28154e7982a86","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Extend AC#5's proving command to: `rg -n 'session-log append|append_session_log' docs/user-guide.md && rg -n 'config.md' docs/user-guide.md`","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a minimal forward pointer (e.g., one sentence or `See docs/ticket-model.md`) in the relevant CLAUDE.md section(s) as part of this story, even if full slimming is deferred to S2, so the new canonical doc is discoverable from the primary agent entry point immediately.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Out: editing CLAUDE.md (that is S2) and any code change.'","'Index docs/ticket-model.md in docs/README.md' is the only inbound-link AC — no AC requires a forward pointer from CLAUDE.md","CLAUDE.md is described as the agent-facing 'root guidance file (S2)'; without a pointer there, agents following CLAUDE.md will not discover the new doc until S2"],"finding":"docs/ticket-model.md will be indexed in docs/README.md but will have no inbound link from CLAUDE.md (edits to CLAUDE.md are explicitly out of scope / deferred to S2). Until S2 runs, the primary agent entry point (CLAUDE.md) contains no pointer to the new canonical concept doc, leaving docs/ticket-model.md navigable only via the docs/ index — not from the agent's natural reading path.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f57d1dfe265d9f353","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section / Acceptance Criteria — 'Index docs/ticket-model.md in docs/README.md' (no corresponding CLAUDE.md forward-pointer)","norm_id":"nfdd9880c1aa5adcb","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["S2 is delayed or descoped — docs/ticket-model.md exists but is unreachable from the primary agent guidance file for an extended period","An agent reads CLAUDE.md for ticket-model concepts and finds the original inline content, unaware the canonical version now lives in docs/ticket-model.md"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In CLAUDE.md, for each section whose content is being homed in docs/ticket-model.md or the other updated docs, append a one-line cross-reference such as '> Canonical reference: docs/ticket-model.md'. This is a minimal edit (not slimming) that keeps S2's scope intact while making the new docs discoverable.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Retitle the story (e.g., 'Create authoritative doc homes for CLAUDE.md content (prereq for S2)') or add a one-sentence note to the title section clarifying that this story only creates destinations and CLAUDE.md cleanup is deferred to S2.","cohort":["E3","E5","G5"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Title: 'Re-home CLAUDE.md-native content into authoritative docs'","Scope section: 'Out: editing CLAUDE.md (that is S2) and any code change. Docs-only.'","After this story, CLAUDE.md content is duplicated, not moved — re-homing is incomplete until S2 runs."],"finding":"The plan title says 'Re-home CLAUDE.md-native content' (implying content moves out of CLAUDE.md), but the Scope section explicitly excludes editing CLAUDE.md ('Out: editing CLAUDE.md — that is S2'). After this story, CLAUDE.md is unchanged and the content exists in both places. The title mis-sets expectations about the end state of this story and could cause a reviewer or downstream agent to expect CLAUDE.md to be slimmed as part of this work.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6f8ab8302f93a5cc","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Title / Scope section ('Out: editing CLAUDE.md (that is S2)')","norm_id":"n002b46cab4d499ec","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A reviewer approves this story expecting CLAUDE.md to be slimmed, then is surprised when S2 arrives and has to explain why the 'rehoming' wasn't done in this story.","An agent executing this story sees the title and attempts to also edit CLAUDE.md, contradicting the explicit out-of-scope constraint."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Change the title to: 'Create authoritative doc destinations for CLAUDE.md content (S2 prereq)' and add to the Why section: 'Note: CLAUDE.md itself is not edited here; this story only creates the receiving docs so S2 can safely remove the source content.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The AC proving command for docs/user-guide.md (`rg -n 'session-log append|append_session_log' docs/user-guide.md`) matches a line that already exists today (user-guide.md:170 has `rebar session-log append …`), so the AC would pass vacuously without the implementer actually moving or expanding the auto-rotation and capture-helper detail from CLAUDE.md. The deliverable intent ('retain the session-log capture-helper section') is broader than what the proving command verifies, leaving the richer auto-rotation content (session fingerprint, pointer semantics, degradation) potentially unwritten.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9a1a46790b505373","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — 'docs/user-guide.md retains the session-log capture-helper section'","norm_id":"n5c108673d760c543","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:cited-reference-inaccurate","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace the proving command with: `rg -n 'auto-rotation|current_session_log|fingerprint' docs/u